      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE ART OF SUCCESS (2) stretched her winning run to six when she led from this draw and kept going to get home by 3.5 metres at this circuit and distance last time. That maintained a perfect record here and she stays in the same grade so will be tough to stop. LE BELLE BIJOUX (1) relished a class drop at this circuit and distance last week, getting the job done by 9 metres. Worked to the front from a wider barrier there so expect her to be prominent from the ace draw. HOORAH PHILTRA (8) is hard knock off a string of top-three results at this circuit and distance. Came from this barrier to miss by only 1.7m two back and won prior. Go well again. DAY TWO (3) owns a solid record at this circuit and distance and has been producing some decent efforts from wider barriers of late including a Wagga win two back.",
